The paper discusses the optimization of spectral efficiency in a heterogeneous network consisting of macro and small base stations, which is a common topic in the field of information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of multiuser MIMO communications is also a key aspect of the paper, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper also involves the analysis of association probabilities and comparison of different scenarios, which can be considered as a game-theoretic problem (cs.GT).
